      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Build the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the {{vegetable-oil}} in a wide pan over medium-high heat. Fry the {{onion}} for 5 minutes until softened. Add the {{garlic}} and {{ginger-root}} and cook for 1 minute. Add the {{cumin-ground}}, {{coriander-ground}}, {{smoked-paprika}}, {{chilli-powder}}, and {{tomato-puree}} and stir for 1 minute until the spices are fragrant. Transfer to the slow cooker. Add the {{lamb-shoulder}}, {{tinned-tomatoes}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Stir to combine. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, until the lamb is completely tender. Switch off, wait 2 minutes, then stir through the {{plain-yoghurt}} and {{garam-masala}}. Taste and adjust seasoning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Switch off the slow cooker and wait 3 to 4 minutes before stirring in the yoghurt. Full-fat plain yoghurt is more stable than low-fat",
              "cause": "Added while the pot was still very hot",
              "symptom": "Yoghurt has curdled in the sauce"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Always fry the spices with the onion and oil before adding them. This step cannot be done in the slow cooker itself",
              "cause": "Spices not bloomed before slow cooking",
              "symptom": "Curry tastes flat and one-dimensional"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Remove the lid and cook on high for 20 to 30 minutes at the end to reduce. Alternatively, stir in 1 tablespoon of tomato puree",
              "cause": "Tinned tomatoes released a lot of water",
              "symptom": "Sauce too thin"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rogan josh is one of the most ordered dishes in British curry houses and one of the most cooked at home. The slow cooker version produces a sauce with more body than a quick pan version because the lamb renders fat into the sauce over six hours. Serve with basmati rice and naan, and spoon mango chutney and yoghurt alongside.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
